
// This Hyperlambda code snippet uses the [add] slot to append nodes to a target node specified by its expression. It retrieves nodes from the [.arguments] node using [get-nodes] for both [order] and [direction] arguments, and adds these nodes to the target node specified in the [add] expression. This allows dynamic modification of the node structure based on input arguments.
add:x:./*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/order
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/direction
